\@writefile{lox}{\contentsline {fixme}{\color  {fxnote}\ignorespaces BW: \citet  {Chao2023} allow for alters with observed exposures equal one to be in fact not exposed to the treated ego (the ego didn't deliver the treatment...), but we exclude such measurement problem by our design. Namely, we only have a one-sided misclassification for alters (0 instead of 1, but not vice versa).}{1}{section.1}\protected@file@percent }
